Notebook[{
Cell["Tropical Operations Tutorial", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"85a39bc8-5be5-4270-9b39-8a6a8924d83e"],

Cell["\<\
Min-plus arithmetic on scalars and matrices: TropicalPlus, TropicalTimes, \
TropicalDot, TropicalMatrixPower. This is sense 1 of \"tropical\" in the \
literature -- the algebraic side. Sense 2 (graph-translated tropical \
convexity: tropical segments, geodesic convex hulls) lives in \
TropicalConvexityGuide / TropicalConvexityTutorial.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9f1dea37-2049-4b5d-92ae-d8d319ee6659"],

Cell["\<\
The bridge between the two senses is the matrix-form triangle inequality: \
tropical matrix powers of the cost-adjacency matrix of a graph converge to \
the graph distance matrix at the diameter step.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7ecff0d8-076a-4871-abef-bfb0c8705fa1"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"cc92e9e5-a989-41f3-b194-6876932f2cfe"],

Cell["Needs[\"WolframInstitute`SyntheticInfrageometry`\"]", "Code",ExpressionUUID->"9b45fc0e-8adb-44d5-ba0d-f11ca4cbb587"],

Cell["Tropical addition (Min on scalars)", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"80b418bc-7f48-4c26-a0fd-f76cba2528cf"],

Cell["\<\
TropicalPlus is min-plus addition: Min on scalars, identity Infinity. \
Listable, so it threads element-wise on equal-shape lists, vectors, or \
matrices.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b9426a89-cd9a-48c6-b433-424a77f16fe4"],

Cell["TropicalPlus[3, 5, 1, 7]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"76826c0f-b648-4c94-bb9c-ec07ef00665e"],

Cell["TropicalPlus[Infinity, 7]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"3aad43d2-7267-4f41-85e8-797aadb8f7ea"],

Cell["\<\
Element-wise on matrices (Min is NOT Listable; TropicalPlus is):\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"1205ceec-42d8-41a0-8963-e184b0a3ca10"],

Cell["TropicalPlus[{{1, 2}, {3, 4}}, {{4, 1}, {2, 5}}]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"5d1a452a-fcc9-463d-9f22-8f172c95a0f9"],

Cell["Tropical multiplication (Plus on scalars)", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"13b330fb-970e-437a-b017-2e8bb65ccb34"],

Cell["\<\
TropicalTimes is min-plus multiplication: Plus on scalars, identity 0. \
Listable.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f60fe1f8-2d8c-439e-afc4-71596689e143"],

Cell["TropicalTimes[2, 3, 5]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"086eedd3-c3bd-4ca2-81b0-374979a77cc5"],

Cell["TropicalTimes[0, 7]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"02a1a774-fe0b-4b67-8e7d-05b4a98b2ce5"],

Cell["Tropical matrix product", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"74d5741b-6543-403e-b76e-ab989ee4d94a"],

Cell["\<\
TropicalDot[A, B] = Inner[Plus, A, B, Min] -- replaces ordinary Plus with Min \
and ordinary Times with Plus in matrix multiplication.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"67c6b5d6-65ae-4a95-bb55-54cf02a2c4b6"],

Cell["A = {{0, 1, Infinity}, {1, 0, 2}, {Infinity, 2, 0}}", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"ee1f1626-0c89-4a6f-9dff-f7f00b14c249"],

Cell["TropicalDot[A, A]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"7d8e2d02-3c15-4999-a086-8b71eddc5c13"],

Cell["Tropical matrix powers", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"9f8a4c54-b27b-4a5d-a7a4-11b9ee8a8f2f"],

Cell["\<\
TropicalMatrixPower[A, k] iterates TropicalDot. The k = 0 case is the \
tropical identity matrix (0 on the diagonal, Infinity elsewhere).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b5e5faeb-7c89-4e94-a126-0936d7e08a77"],

Cell["TropicalMatrixPower[A, 0]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"cad38aee-0d24-4493-80cd-20c209aad1b2"],

Cell["TropicalMatrixPower[A, 2]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"aaaed6d1-5f77-4009-83d0-c1fce0bfc70a"],

Cell["The A -> D relation", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"a3a40ffe-7a7b-40d1-b9fd-82c4bd9d54dc"],

Cell["\<\
The cost-adjacency matrix of a graph is the adjacency matrix with 0 -> \
Infinity and 1 -> edge cost. Tropical-iterating it converges to the graph \
distance matrix at the diameter step.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"cb234dda-f656-43c4-86b3-4d7f3ec900b4"],

Cell["g = GridGraph[{3, 3}]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"68769f0b-3fc2-4074-8ef5-54464037a3b8"],

Cell["\<\
costA = AdjacencyMatrix[g] /. {0 -> Infinity, 1 -> 1}; distD = \
GraphDistanceMatrix[g];\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"4fa08f31-898a-4712-922b-4317a7fcd032"],

Cell["TropicalMatrixPower[costA, GraphDiameter[g]] == distD", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"e02bf354-8401-4385-a2e6-4ff7c26269a8"],

Cell["\<\
The convergence is sharp: at the diameter minus one, the iteration has not \
yet stabilised.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"2f60b000-f7d4-4242-a48d-dfc98bf3e159"],

Cell["TropicalMatrixPower[costA, GraphDiameter[g] - 1] != distD", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"8d04a156-a713-4e62-89ce-844b076cac17"],

Cell["Past the diameter the iteration is stable.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"fb7c9e86-0066-4fc3-9eff-752a14ab5e4a"],

Cell["TropicalMatrixPower[costA, GraphDiameter[g] + 5] == distD", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"0ecc0fd1-76e5-4aae-a204-30b88ddaae0d"],

Cell["The matrix-form triangle inequality", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"0c86608a-0c00-47d2-a10f-b9c114803e91"],

Cell["\<\
A graph distance matrix D satisfies TropicalDot[D, D] === D -- the matrix \
form of the triangle inequality in the min-plus semiring.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"764aa864-37b0-4155-a153-e4d814329114"],

Cell["TropicalDot[distD, distD] == distD", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"a04264ca-dba1-491b-ba07-6bf9af1c349e"],

Cell["\<\
This idempotence is exactly the predicate DistanceMatrixQ from the \
MetricAlgebra layer.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8f5b28ee-3eed-4ac9-a592-b1192c125f93"],

Cell["DistanceMatrixQ[distD]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"bfa83dd0-b609-4023-82fc-ad901a13f3c9"],

Cell["Step-by-step convergence on a cycle", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"0dbd80e1-021b-4523-a606-bc4e89e92683"],

Cell["Watch the iteration converge step by step on a 6-cycle.", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b56cfc6d-fe60-40e5-89ae-d5f7da49e805"],

Cell["c6 = CycleGraph[6]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"30c9c5bd-523f-426b-a99c-1a31b1b395d9"],

Cell["c6costA = AdjacencyMatrix[c6] /. {0 -> Infinity, 1 -> 1};", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"85cbe378-ab89-406a-b1f5-4da00262f833"],

Cell["\<\
NestList[TropicalDot[#, c6costA] &, c6costA, GraphDiameter[c6]] // \
Map[MatrixForm]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"6a6375f0-f1c0-4407-b688-499704ee068e"],

Cell["\<\
At each iteration k, the (i, j) entry holds the length of the shortest path \
of at most k edges from i to j. At k = diameter the matrix is the full \
distance matrix.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"39d18c64-9168-4485-992e-01860ef06d53"],

Cell["See also", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"158e0cbc-1d33-438a-8d42-0239fc993249"],

Cell["TropicalOperationsGuide -- categorical overview.", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"2e3ed7e5-d4ec-4bc0-845a-1cafd2ebe5e5"],

Cell["\<\
TropicalConvexityGuide -- the graph-translated convexity layer (sense 2).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"69acc042-3aec-427d-8e2b-587a062f8fce"],

Cell["\<\
MetricAlgebraGuide -- DistanceMatrixQ, MetricInterval, GeodesicCount.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"3438d633-563a-4bbf-8a42-14249bf11c4b"],

Cell["References", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"a2abc5fc-9424-48d3-8ed9-fb51f812c5e0"],

Cell["\<\
Maclagan and Sturmfels, Introduction to Tropical Geometry, AMS GSM 161, 2015, \
https://janos.cs.technion.ac.il/COURSES/238900-13/Tropical/MaclaganSturmfels.\
pdf\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"c144c904-3655-4b76-b5b3-e3a3067d66e1"],

Cell["\<\
Cuninghame-Green, Minimax Algebra, Lecture Notes in Economics and \
Mathematical Systems 166, Springer 1979 (origin of the matrix-form min-plus \
algebra).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"7ede5289-35bb-47ce-9f30-dd90635622a8"],

Cell["\<\
Butkovic, Max-linear Systems: Theory and Algorithms, Springer 2010.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"72b3d6f1-5124-42f5-8591-1ae407a0bc2d"]
},
